Defendant in custody on WRIT.  
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing after revocation, his probation having been revoked effective 11-21-16.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of five and one-half (5 1/2) years, concurrent with Case Nos. 09 CF 137 and 10 CF 283.   Two and one-half (2 1/2) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Pay restitution to Collins State Bank in the amount of $3,052.80; 
2) Maintain full-time employment or work search; 
3) No leaving or changing of employment without disclosure to the agent and with agents approval;
4) No contact with Collins State Bank; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Defendant is entitled to 292 days sentence credit.   
